After you install or update TAS for VMs, you can deploy the TAS Portal.
For information about configuring TAS Portal and the app accelerators, see:

* [Configure App Accelerators on TAS Portal (beta)](./configure-tas-portal.html.md.erb)
* [Runtime Resources plug-in (beta)](./runtime-resource-visibility.html.md.erb)


## <a id="deploy"></a> Deploy TAS portal

1. After installing or updating TAS for VMs, you see the **Review Pending Changes** screen.

2. Click the **TAS Portal Errand** check box.

   Deploy the `tas-portal` application under the `system` space of the `system` org.

3. Click **Apply Changes**.


## <a id="remove"></a> Deactivate TAS portal

There are two ways to deactivate the TAS Portal:

* Delete the `tas-portal` application.
* On the **Review Pending Changes** screen, deselect **TAS Portal Errand**, and click **Apply Changes**.
